---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Book a 60-Minute AI Risk Audit"
  description="Book a 60-minute AI risk audit with Christian Kameir — a review of your PI firm's current AI use across intake, drafting, discovery, and advertising, with a written gap analysis. $750."
>
  <article class="aie-call">
    <div class="container">

      <header class="aie-call__header">
        <p class="label"><a href="/ai-ethics">Ethics Safe AI Use for Law Firms</a></p>
        <h1 class="aie-call__title">60-Minute AI Risk Audit</h1>
        <p class="aie-call__price">$750</p>
        <p class="aie-call__sub">
          A review of your firm's current AI use across intake, drafting, discovery,
          and advertising — with a written gap analysis and the specific protocols
          to address your highest-priority exposures.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <div class="aie-call__body prose">
        <p>
          The session covers the six risk areas the playbook maps: intake and UPL
          exposure, demand letter verification, pleadings and citation protocols,
          discovery and PHI handling, client communication, and advertising copy review.
        </p>
        <p>
          You receive a written summary within 48 hours: your firm's current exposure
          by category, scored Red/Yellow/Green, with the specific protocol or policy
          document each Red and Yellow item requires.
        </p>
        <p>
          Sessions are conducted via video conference. Scheduling is confirmed
          by email within one business day of booking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aie-call__cta">
        <!-- CALENDLY or BOOKING LINK: replace href with your scheduling URL -->
        <!-- Suggested: Calendly embed or link, pre-filled with "AI Risk Audit" -->
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Request a booking</a>
        <p class="aie-call__cta-note">
          Use the contact form. Include your firm name, approximate number of
          attorneys, and a brief description of your current AI use.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <div class="aie-call__also">
        <p class="label">Also available</p>
        <p>
          <strong>Firm-wide staff training</strong> — 2-hour remote workshop, up to
          25 attendees. Covers the policy, the verification protocol, PHI handling,
          and advertising rules. Written materials included. $2,500.
          <a href="/contact">Inquire via contact form.</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="aie-call__disclaimer">
        <em>Informational only. Not legal advice. Ethics rules vary by jurisdiction.</em><br>
        Christian Kameir &thinsp;·&thinsp; © 2026 Decentralized Publishing LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>

    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
.aie-call__header {
  padding-top: 4rem;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-m);
}

.aie-call__title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.aie-call__price {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.aie-call__sub {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 520px;
}

.aie-call__body {
  padding-block: var(--space-l);
  max-width: 560px;
  font-size: 0.97rem;
}

.aie-call__cta {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 2rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.aie-call__cta-note {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  max-width: 380px;
}

.aie-call__also {
  padding-block: var(--space-m);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 540px;
}

.aie-call__also .label {
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.aie-call__disclaimer {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
}
</style>
